comments: Holiday (HOU) avoids stepping out of bounds while still in possession of the ball.
Brooks (HOU) gathers the ball on his right foot and hops consecutively on it.
Green (HOU) momentarily places a resting hand onto Barnes' (TOR) back and marginal contact occurs in the post.
Barnes (TOR) moves alongside Brooks' (HOU) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Holiday (HOU) is moving alongside Barrett's (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Smith Jr. (HOU) legally contests Trent Jr.'s (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Brooks (HOU) and Poeltl (TOR) come together during the loose ball and the contact is incidental.
Quickley (TOR) brings his off-arm toward Brooks (HOU) as he releases away, but Brooks is not dislodged from his position.
Thompson (HOU) reaches in and initiates contact to Quickley's (TOR) face, affecting his SQBR.

Replay review of the foul called on Holiday (HOU) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Holiday reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball and any further contact with Barnes (TOR) is marginal.  Houston is awarded possession of the ball, as it was imminent they would gain possession at the time of the whistle.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Barnes (TOR) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  There is no clear and conclusive evidence to overturn the call on the floor that Barnes is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Barnes (TOR) legally contests Brooks' (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Thompson (HOU) commits a take foul on Barrett (TOR).
Quickley (TOR) legally contests Holiday's (HOU) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
